gomodel:SYNGO_5543  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1C: MINK and TNIK enriched in PSD biochemical fractions prepared from rat brain, as compared to S1, S2, P1, P2 fractions.\n\nFigure 1D: In cultured hippocampal neurons at DIV23, a polyclonal antibody against MINK/TNIK showed localization to synaptic puncta (co-staining with Bassoon and Phalloidin, resolution does not allow for distinction between pre/post-synapse).\n\nFigure 2C: RNAi knockdown of MINK in hippocampal cultures after 18 DIV significantly reduced dendritic arbor complexity relative to control neurons.\n\nFigure 3: MINK and TNIK knockdown modulate spine density and surface expression of AMPA receptors.\n\nFigure 4: MINK and TNIK localization in neurons is modulated by the activation state of Rap2.\n\nFigure 6: MINK blocks Rap2-mediated reduction in surface GluR1 clusters.. Experimental description: Figure 1: \"Western blot analysis of postnuclear supernatants isolated from adult rat tissues.\"\n\n\"MINK RNAi: 5'-GATCCCCGTACTCTCACCATCGCAATTTCAAGAGAATTGCGATGGTGAGAGTACTTTTTGGAAA-3' and 5'-AGCTTTTCCAAAAAGTACTCTCACCATCGCAATTCTCTTGAAATTGCGATGGTGAGAGTACGGG-3'. MINK RNAi sequences previously validated by (McCarty et al., 2005) were adapted for insertion into pSuper.\"\n\nantibody:\nMINK and MINK/TNIK antibodies from GeneTex" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_5543" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

